e interests of patriarchy, heteronormativity, nationalism, racism, and ableism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aHebrew literature, Moderny20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSex crimes in literature. 0aViolence in literature. 4aArea Studies : Israel Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aLiterature : Hebrew Language and Literature. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aSociology : Violence. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848457040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438484570423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438484570/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles